    {
      "kind": "list",
      "heading": "The 25 Most Anticipated Movies of 2025",
      "note": "Sean picked 12, Amanda picked 12, and they chose the 25th together",
      "picks": [
        {
          "title": "Eddington",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Sean Fennessey",
          "note": "No. 12. Ari Aster's black-comedy Western: Joaquin Phoenix, Pedro Pascal, Emma Stone, Austin Butler, shot by Darius Khondji. A New Mexico sheriff with higher aspirations."
        },
        {
          "title": "M3GAN 2.0",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Amanda Dobbins",
          "note": "No. 12. Akela Cooper writing again, Allison Williams back, dated June 27. 'It's Ma-toogan to me.'"
        },
        {
          "title": "Mother Mary",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Sean Fennessey",
          "note": "No. 11. David Lowery's epic melodrama: Anne Hathaway as a pop star, Michaela Coel as a fashion designer, songs by Jack Antonoff and Charli XCX."
        },
        {
          "title": "Hamnet",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Amanda Dobbins",
          "note": "No. 11. Chloé Zhao's adaptation of the Maggie O'Farrell novel, with Paul Mescal as Shakespeare and Jessie Buckley as Agnes. Only this low because Amanda knows how sad it is."
        },
        {
          "title": "A Big Bold Beautiful Journey",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Sean Fennessey",
          "note": "No. 10. Kogonada's follow-up to After Yang: Margot Robbie's first lead since Barbie, opposite Colin Farrell. The kind of star-driven original Sean keeps asking studios to make."
        },
        {
          "title": "Die My Love",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Amanda Dobbins",
          "note": "No. 10. Lynne Ramsay's first film since You Were Never Really Here: Jennifer Lawrence and Robert Pattinson, postpartum psychosis, relocated from France to Montana."
        },
        {
          "title": "Superman",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Sean Fennessey",
          "note": "No. 9. James Gunn's, out July 11, with David Corenswet. Sean wants to be inspired and doesn't care about the suit discourse."
        },
        {
          "title": "Blue Moon",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Amanda Dobbins",
          "note": "No. 9. Richard Linklater on Lorenz Hart and the opening night of Oklahoma!, with Ethan Hawke as Hart and Andrew Scott as Oscar Hammerstein II. Rumored for Cannes."
        },
        {
          "title": "Nouvelle Vague",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Amanda Dobbins",
          "note": "No. 9 (the other half). Linklater's second 2025 film, the making of Breathless, with Zoey Deutch."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Mastermind",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Sean Fennessey",
          "note": "No. 8. Kelly Reichardt's art-heist movie set against the Vietnam War: Josh O'Connor, John Magaro, Gaby Hoffmann, Bill Camp, Alana Haim."
        },
        {
          "title": "Paper Tiger",
          "year": 2026,
          "by": "Amanda Dobbins",
          "note": "No. 8. James Gray's two-brothers crime story with Adam Driver, Jeremy Strong, and Anne Hathaway. Hasn't shot yet, likely 2026."
        },
        {
          "title": "Sentimental Value",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Sean Fennessey",
          "note": "No. 7. Joachim Trier reunites with Renate Reinsve and co-writer Eskil Vogt after The Worst Person in the World. Stellan Skarsgård, Elle Fanning, Cory Michael Smith."
        },
        {
          "title": "Mickey 17",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Amanda Dobbins",
          "note": "No. 7. Bong Joon-ho's Parasite follow-up with Robert Pattinson, finally landing March 7 after countless date moves."
        },
        {
          "title": "Highest 2 Lowest",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Sean Fennessey",
          "note": "No. 6. Spike Lee remaking Kurosawa's High and Low for Apple and A24: Denzel Washington, Jeffrey Wright, Ice Spice, A$AP Rocky."
        },
        {
          "title": "After the Hunt",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Amanda Dobbins",
          "note": "No. 6. Luca Guadagnino's campus MeToo drama: Julia Roberts, Ayo Edebiri, Andrew Garfield, Michael Stuhlbarg, Chloë Sevigny, score by Reznor and Ross."
        },
        {
          "title": "Sinners",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Sean Fennessey",
          "note": "No. 5. Ryan Coogler's period vampire movie, Michael B. Jordan as twins. Coogler negotiated to own the film after 25 years."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Phoenician Scheme",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Amanda Dobbins",
          "note": "No. 5. Wes Anderson's espionage comedy: Benicio del Toro, Michael Cera, Bill Murray, Tom Hanks, Scarlett Johansson, and the usual sprawling ensemble."
        },
        {
          "title": "28 Years Later",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Sean Fennessey",
          "note": "No. 4. Danny Boyle and Alex Garland's return to the trilogy, out June 20. Someone told Sean it's the best script they'd read in five years."
        },
        {
          "title": "Black Bag",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Amanda Dobbins",
          "note": "No. 4. Steven Soderbergh's spy thriller: Cate Blanchett and Michael Fassbender, married spies, written by David Koepp. Out March 14."
        },
        {
          "title": "Mission: Impossible - The Final Reckoning",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Sean Fennessey",
          "note": "No. 3. Sean never abandoned the franchise and never will. The trailer made Amanda cry in a theater at 10 a.m."
        },
        {
          "title": "Materialists",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Amanda Dobbins",
          "note": "No. 3. Celine Song's follow-up to Past Lives: a matchmaker between Chris Evans and Pedro Pascal, with Dakota Johnson."
        },
        {
          "title": "Marty Supreme",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Sean Fennessey",
          "note": "No. 2. Josh Safdie's first feature since Uncut Gems: Timothée Chalamet as a 1950s ping-pong hustler, with Gwyneth Paltrow. Dated for Christmas."
        },
        {
          "title": "Opus",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Amanda Dobbins",
          "note": "No. 2. Mark Anthony Green's A24 horror debut with John Malkovich and Ayo Edebiri, premiering at Sundance. Amanda's very good friend directed it."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Battle of Baktan Cross",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Sean Fennessey",
          "note": "No. 1. Paul Thomas Anderson's new film, out August 8: Leonardo DiCaprio, Regina Hall, Sean Penn, Teyana Taylor, Benicio del Toro. Maybe a Vineland adaptation."
        },
        {
          "title": "F1",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Amanda Dobbins",
          "note": "No. 1. Joseph Kosinski and Brad Pitt's $350M racing spectacle, June 27. Amanda plans to catch it at Cannes."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Drama",
          "year": 2025,
          "by": "Sean & Amanda",
          "note": "The 25th, chosen together from the honorable mentions. Christopher Borgli's new film with Robert Pattinson and Zendaya: movie stars and an original story they don't know much about."
        }
      ]
    },
